label scene4:
    
    voice "C-4-1.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "Well, I'm sorry to have pried."

    hide emmeline_young_angry

    show emmeline_young_sad

    "Emmeline's face softens."

    voice "C-4-2.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Really, it's fine. It's nice to get to talk about it with someone."

    voice "C-4-3.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "I take it there aren't too many new opportunities to talk to people here in Cedar?"

    voice "C-4-4.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Not here, no."

    voice "C-4-5.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "Can I ask how you ended up here?"

    voice "C-4-6.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "You could, but it's not a fun story. You can imagine my parents weren't very big fans of my expulsion."

    voice "C-4-7.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "I figured."
    
    play music "music/Age of Transition - Intro.ogg" fadein 1.0 loop
    queue music "music/Age of Transition - Loop.ogg"

    voice "C-4-8.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "They were livid. Engorged with rage. You'd think they were going to eat me, they were so angry."

    voice "C-4-9.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Like they were going to lock me up in the cellar and bury the key."

    "While she's talking, her voice becomes strained. Obviously this is reopening old wounds for her. I feel bad for bringing it up now."

    voice "C-4-10.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "They started pressuring me to find a husband."
    
    voice "C-4-11.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Showed me off to any rich young men or family friends who came by, trying to convince me to give myself up and marry a complete stranger."

    voice "C-4-12.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Made me feel like I was a hunk of meat being peddled in some marketplace. To them, my failure had branded me a commodity. I'd become a damaged good."

    voice "C-4-13.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Something to be sold off, my value to be measured in nothing but the children I would bear."

    voice "C-4-14.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "I couldn't take it. I absolutely couldn't live like that."

    voice "C-4-15.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "So you took off?"

    voice "C-4-16.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "You could tell?"
    
    voice "C-4-17.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "You seem the type."
    
    hide emmeline_young_sad
    
    stop music fadeout 1.0
    
    show emmeline_young_happy

    "This makes Emmeline loosen up again, but only a little. That's good. I have to try and help her feel better. I hope I didn't spoil her night."

    voice "C-4-18.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "I'll go ahead and take that as a compliment."

    voice "C-4-19.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "Good. It was meant as one."

    voice "C-4-20.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "..."

    voice "C-4-21.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "I hadn't meant to bring up bad memories."

    voice "C-4-22.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Like I said, it's fine. It's nice to finally be able to talk to someone about it. It's all been bottled up so long."

    voice "C-4-23.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "I know how you feel."

    voice "C-4-24.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "You can keep going, if you'd like."
    
    play music "music/Departure.ogg" fadein 1.0 loop
    
    voice "C-4-25.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Well, the rest is a lot of the same."

    voice "C-4-26.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "I packed up some clothes and some books and snuck out in the middle of the night."

    voice "C-4-27.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "I stayed in the city a while, with friends and the like. Figured it was the safest way. After sometime though, I knew I had to get farther away than that."
    
    voice "C-4-28.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Somewhere my parents wouldn't find me."

    voice "C-4-29.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "So I ran. Wandered from place to place. Took cabs and buses when I could, walked when I couldn't. Hitchhiked when I absolutely needed to."

    voice "C-4-30.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "It wasn't too safe and as a girl, I had to be careful. But I was smart. I kept my eyes open and it's taken me this far."

    voice "C-4-31.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "How far is 'this far?'"

    voice "C-4-32.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Far enough."

    hide emmeline_young_happy

    show emmeline_young_angry

    voice "C-4-33.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "But..."

    voice "C-4-34.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "But?"
    
    voice "C-4-35.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "I don't know."

    voice "C-4-36.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "I called my parents a few times, just to let them know I was still alive. I'm a good girl like that."

    voice "C-4-37.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "At first, they were even more furious than they'd been while I was at home. They threatened to call the police after me."
    
    voice "C-4-38.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Threatened me when I said I wouldn't come home."

    voice "C-4-39.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "But after some time, as I got farther and farther from home, as I was gone for longer and longer? They started to soften up."

    voice "C-4-40.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Hot rage turned to bold resentment. Resentment turned to disappointment. Disappointment turned to sadness. Turned to regret. Turned to apology..."

    voice "C-4-41.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "...turned to them begging me to come home."

    "Emmeline looked visibly shaken."

    "I felt so bad for her."

    "But I knew how she felt, and I knew I had to let her finish."

    voice "C-4-42.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "..."

    voice "C-4-43.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "It's been more than two years since I left home."

    voice "C-4-44.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "They started begging by the end of the first year. I couldn't take it, so I stopped calling them."

    voice "C-4-45.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "I haven't spoken to them since."

    "Emmeline gazes into her reflection caught on the polish of her empty glass, warm under the dim bar lights."

    "The night has gone on and many have left. Everything's quieter now."

    "Everything is moving softer, going slower, like the night has entered into a dreamlike state."

    "I place a hand on Emmeline's shoulder softly. I want to comfort her."

    voice "C-4-46.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "You don't want to go home?"

    voice "C-4-47.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "No, I do. Believe me. This sort of life gets tiring after a while. Having no safety, no security. Always needing to move from place to place."
    
    voice "C-4-48.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Searching for warmth every single night and praying every single morning you'll be able to find work and to feed yourself..."

    voice "C-4-49.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "It drains you. It takes a lot away and it makes you lose your sense of place."

    voice "C-4-50.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "When you can't ever stay in one place too long, it feels like everything in your life has a time limit set on it."
    
    voice "C-4-51.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "It ticks away, and it couldn't care less about what you want. The time runs out, and one by one, everything in your life melts away."

    voice "C-4-52.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "The people you meet, the things you gain, the sights you see. They leave, and you're left with nothing again."

    voice "C-4-53.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "And do you know what you do then?"

    voice "C-4-54.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "Yeah."

    voice "C-4-55.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "You start over. You feel like you don't have any control over anything, like you're not even the person living your life."
    
    voice "C-4-56.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "You feel like you're only sitting back and watching events unfold. Like you're an observer from the outside, looking in on yourself."
    
    hide emmeline_young_angry
    
    show emmeline_young_surprise

    "Emmeline seems surprised. It looks like I've understood her perfectly well."

    voice "C-4-57.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Right, that's... how I feel. Thank you."

    voice "C-4-58.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "Don't mention it."
    
    hide emmeline_young_surprise

    show emmeline_young_sad

    voice "C-4-59.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "That's truly how I feel. And I hate it, and I want to stop, and I want to go home, but... I can't."

    voice "C-4-60.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "I just... can't go home."

    voice "C-4-61.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "I don't have it in me to go home."

    voice "C-4-62.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "You're afraid of what will happen if you do?"

    voice "C-4-63.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "I'm beyond afraid. I'm petrified. I can't even breathe right when I think about seeing my parents again."
    
    voice "C-4-64.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Even though this journey's taken so much away from me, I feel like just giving up and returning home isn't going to give me any of that back."

    voice "C-4-65.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "It isn't."

    voice "C-4-66.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "I feel like, if I want to get back everything that's been drained out of me, I need to find something."

    voice "C-4-67.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "I don't know what, just that it's something I'm searching for."

    voice "C-4-68.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "And if I find it, I can go back and live a normal life again."

    "Emmeline sighs."

    voice "C-4-69.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "...If any of that makes sense to you."

    play music "music/Theme for a Wanderer Rework.mp3" fadein 1.0 loop
    #queue music "music/Theme for a Wanderer - Loop.ogg"

    "I try to assure her."

    voice "C-4-70.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "Really, I understand. I'm in the same situation as you. I am."

    hide emmeline_young_sad

    show emmeline_young_surprise

    voice "C-4-71.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "You're a runaway too?"

    "I shrug."

    voice "C-4-72.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "Something like that. But I can't say much."

    hide emmeline_young_surprise

    show emmeline_young_happy

    voice "C-4-73.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Well, that's not suspicious."

    voice "C-4-74.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "No, it's nothing like that. I'm not a criminal."

    voice "C-4-75.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Obviously."

    voice "C-4-76.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "I'm not. I'm clean. I just... need to travel a lot. It's something I have to do. I go from place to place, like you, and I search for things."

    voice "C-4-77.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "I'm like you."

    voice "C-4-78.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "..."

    voice "C-4-79.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Don't worry, I know you're like me."

    voice "C-4-80.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "I don't know if I knew before we started talking, but I definitely know now. I think that's why I've told you so much about myself."
    
    voice "C-4-81.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "I've never spoken so much about myself before. Not to anyone. Not in my whole life. I've never spoken much at all, really."

    "So I've heard."

    voice "C-4-82.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "So that's alright. You don't have to explain yourself to me. Consider it an apology for me spending the last hour talking about nothing but myself. I'm sorry for that."

    "I dismiss her with a wave."

    voice "C-4-83.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "Really, it's fine. I don't think I've ever talked to anyone like this either. And I'm glad I could help you finally open up about these things."

    "Emmeline beams."

    voice "C-4-84.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "Mhm."

    voice "C-4-85.mp3" #Emmeline (Hayley Nelson)
    emm "And it's all thanks to the fact that you liked my singing so much you needed to tell me, huh?"

    "I laughed."

    voice "C-4-86.mp3" #Wayfarer (Terrance Drye)
    wan "Well, I did say you have a beautiful voice."
    
    scene black
    
    stop music fadeout 1.0
    
    jump scene5
